    dc:creator "Faustino-Magalhaes, Mayara D.", "Piacentini, Luis N.", "Santos, Adalberto J." ;
    dc:date "2024" ;
    dc:title "The desert wolf-spider genus Xenoctenus: two endemic species from the Brazilian Caatinga, and a redescription of the type-species, X. unguiculatus (Araneae: Xenoctenidae)" ;
    bibo:endPage "539" ;
    bibo:issue "5" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2024-01-16" ;
    bibo:startPage "517" ;
    bibo:volume "5399" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517348>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517350>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517352>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517354>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517356>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517358>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517370>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517376>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517382>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517384> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517348>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Xenoctenus spp., habitus of live specimens. A–E, Xenoctenus vittatus (Mello-Leit„o, 1936) comb. nov. A, male and B, female from Guanambi, Bahia, Brazil (UFMG 20929). C, male (UFMG 24328) and D, female (UFMG 24330) from Brumado, Bahia, Brazil. E, male from Itaguaçu da Bahia, Bahia, Brazil (UFMG 20535). F, Xenoctenus unguiculatus Mello- Leit„o, 1938, female from Parque Nacional Sierra de las Quijadas, San Luis, Argentina (MACN-Ar 45013). Photos by Pedro H. Martins (C, D), Leonardo S. Carvalho (A, B, E) and Hernán Iuri (F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517348/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517350>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Xenoctenus unguiculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1938, juvenile holotype (MLP 14093). A, C, habitus dorsal view. B, prosoma, frontal view. D, habitus, ventral view. E, original collection labels." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517350/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517352>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Xenoctenus marmoratus Mello-Leit„o, 1941, juvenile holotype (MLP 14835). A, habitus, lateral view. B, prosoma, frontal view. C, habitus, dorsal view. D, habitus, ventral view. E, original collection vial with labels." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517352/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517354>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Xenoctenus unguiculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1938. Male from Reserva Natural y Cultural Bosques Telteca, Mendoza, Argentina (MACN-Ar 35619).A, palp, prolateral. B, ventral. C, retrolateral. D, habitus, dorsal view.Abbreviations: E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; RTP, retrolateral tegular projection; StLL, subtegular locking lobe. White star on tegular distal division (TDD)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517354/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517356>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Xenoctenus unguiculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1938, male from PN Sierra de las Quijadas, San Luis, Argentina (MACN- Ar 45013).A, C, palp.A, prolateral. B, ventral. C, retrolateral.Abbreviations:C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RTP, retrolateral tegular projection. White star on tegular distal division (TDD)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517356/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517358>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Xenoctenus unguiculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1938, female epigynum (A, C) and internal genitalia (B, D). A, B, female from Caucete, San Juan, Argentina (MACN-Ar 35624). A, ventral. B, dorsal. C, D, female from PN Sierra de las Quijadas, San Luis, Argentina (MACN-Ar 45013). C, ventral. D, dorsal. Abbreviations: CD, copulatory ducts; LL, lateral lobes; LLE, lateral lobes extension; MF, median field; S1, primary spermathecae; S2, secondary spermathecae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517358/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517370>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Xenoctenus kaatinga Faustino-Magalhaes & Santos sp. nov., male from Alvorada do Gurguéia, Piauí, Brazil (CNHUFPI 2450).A–C, bleached palp. A, prolateral. B, ventral. C, retrolateral. D. habitus, dorsal.Abbreviations: C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RTP, retrolateral tegular projection; StLL, subtegular locking lobe. White star on tegular distal division (TDD)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517370/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517376>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Xenoctenus kaatinga Faustino-Magalhaes & Santos sp. nov., male and female from Alvorada do Gurguéia, Piauí, Brazil (CNHUFPI 2448). A–B, expanded, bleached male palp. A, prolateral. B, retrolateral. C, bleached female epigynum, ventral. D, bleached internal female genitalia, dorsal. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; ELL, embolar locked lobe; LL, lateral lobes; LLE, lateral lobes extension; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; RTP; retrolateral tegular projection; S1, primary spermathecae; S2, secondary spermathecae; St, subtegulum, StLL, subtegular locking lobe; T, tegulum. White star on tegular distal division (TDD)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517376/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517382>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Geographic distribution records of Xenoctenus Mello-Leit„o, 1938 in South America." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517382/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10517384>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Geographic distribution records of Xenoctenus unguiculatus Mello-Leit„o, 1938 inArgentina and southern Brazil. The “?” indicates that the specific locality is unknown as it was reported only as the Province of Buenos Aires." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10517384/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

